Australia made 459 all out in reply to Pakistan’s first innings total of 476-4 declared in the opening test in Rawalpindi on Tuesday. Usman Khawaja top scored for the tourists with a fluent 97 while Marnus Labuschagne (90), David Warner (68) and Steve Smith (78) also scored half-centuries. Left-arm spinner Nauman Ali was Pakistan’s most successful bowler, claiming 6-107. Five wickets for Nauman Ali! That's a great effort on this pitch #PAKvAUS pic.twitter.com/LxDmueLfIy — cricket.com.au (@cricketcomau) March 8, 2022 